<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-10-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="987" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d987">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Peirce</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy
                                        of the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St.
                                        Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-10-30"><hi rend="italic">October 30,
                                1899</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>[Mr. Peirce reports that the provision, fourth paragraph, second page of
                            the protocol, which is objectionable to the Department, is to be
                            omitted.]</p>
